00:03:12,331 --> 00:03:18,435
About 10 years ago, Susanna Morgan was running a food bank in Alaska, and she really needed fresh produce.

40
00:03:18,875 --> 00:03:19,716
She always did.

41
00:03:20,356 --> 00:03:21,457
One day, the phone rang.

42
00:03:21,617 --> 00:03:24,819
It was this big national charity called Feeding America.

43
00:03:25,139 --> 00:03:29,262
Feeding America is this network of food banks all around the country, including Susanna's.

44
00:03:29,582 --> 00:03:33,625
And what they do is they get these big donations of food, and they figure out where they should go.

45
00:03:34,205 --> 00:03:36,307
On this call, they said they had a big donation for her.

46
00:03:36,667 --> 00:03:37,708
It was not fresh produce.

47
00:03:38,108 --> 00:03:40,910
It was a truckload of five gallon buckets of pickles.

48
00:03:41,190 --> 00:03:43,631
You're kidding me, you're offering me pickles?

49
00:03:46,191 --> 00:03:52,253
And the feeding American person who said, yeah, I know, I know, I know, but you guys have been hanging out there at the top of the list for quite a while.

50
00:03:52,313 --> 00:03:56,034
And this is the first thing we've had that we think we'll really make it all the way to Alaska.

51
00:03:56,495 --> 00:03:57,515
And what did you do with them?

52
00:03:58,235 --> 00:04:02,916
We strong armed every soup kitchen we could find into taking pickles.

53
00:04:05,097 --> 00:04:08,919
Susanna would ask the people from Feeding America, why aren't we getting more fresh produce?

54
00:04:09,179 --> 00:04:16,403
Feeding America would say, well, we didn't offer you that truckload of oranges out of California because we thought the transportation would be too expensive.

55
00:04:16,483 --> 00:04:18,063
And I would say, ah!

56
00:04:18,584 --> 00:04:19,324
That scream there?

57
00:04:19,544 --> 00:04:28,488
That's because Susanna had set up her own transportation system so that if Feeding America had offered her fresh fruits or vegetables, she could get them trucked to Alaska really cheaply.

58
00:04:28,809 --> 00:04:31,630
But the people at the Feeding America Home Office didn't know that.

59
00:04:31,950 --> 00:04:33,873
And a lot of food banks had this problem.

60
00:04:34,213 --> 00:04:39,281
One food bank director in Idaho, my home state, complained that he got a truckload of potatoes.

61
00:04:39,741 --> 00:04:41,063
I mean, come on, it's Idaho.

62
00:04:41,183 --> 00:04:45,610
Of course, he already had a warehouse full of potatoes that had been donated by local farmers.

63
00:04:46,115 --> 00:04:50,058
This system had real consequences for hungry people all over the country.

64
00:04:50,439 --> 00:04:53,641
It meant that people in Alaska were not getting fresh produce.

65
00:04:53,661 --> 00:04:55,143
We're not getting, say, potatoes.

66
00:04:55,643 --> 00:04:59,747
And at the same time, the food bank in Idaho had too many potatoes and not enough other stuff.

67
00:04:59,947 --> 00:05:01,268
Everybody knew this was a problem.

68
00:05:01,548 --> 00:05:03,690
But for a long time, they just slipped with it.

69
