And Canis and Susanna and the others, they designed the system this way so that people couldn't just wait until the last second and bid one more fake dollar to get what they wanted.

190
00:13:53,946 --> 00:13:55,728
So it's a sealed bid auction.

191
00:13:55,948 --> 00:13:59,673
You put a number in and wait, and when the auction's done, you see if you won.

192
00:14:00,058 --> 00:14:05,962
The system does tell Tristan that, on average, truckloads of cereal like this one have sold for 4,400 shares.

193
00:14:06,402 --> 00:14:10,985
I currently have about 5,400 shares, so I'm gonna bid all of my shares.

194
00:14:11,085 --> 00:14:12,486
You're going all in for the cereal?

195
00:14:12,606 --> 00:14:18,030
Yeah, I'm gonna go all in, and even going all in, this is no guarantee that I'll get it.

196
00:14:18,330 --> 00:14:20,492
Tristan types in his bid, clicks Submit.

197
00:14:20,792 --> 00:14:23,994
Now it's a waiting game, crossing fingers and hoping for the best.

198
